title: Bucs pounds Princeton in middle school action
text:
Staff photo by Jon Bolt Middle schoolers.. 
Bluefield Middle School’s Devin Lester gets past Princeton’s J.J. Davis, behind Lester, and tries to elude Devin West (29) during the Buccaneers’ 42-8 win over Princeton on Thursday at Mitchell Stadium. Posted: Thursday, October 15, 2015 11:42 pm Bucs pounds Princeton in middle school action Staff reports bdtonline.com 
BLUEFIELD — Malcolm Miller scored two touchdowns and Devin Lester threw for two more to lead Bluefield Middle School to a 42-8 win over Princeton on Thursday night at Mitchell Stadium. 
Miller had scoring runs of 12 and 7 yards, and Lester completed scoring passes to Isaiah Rivers from 48 yards and connected with Jahiem House from 52. Rivers also returned a kick 62 yards for a score. 
Tony Webster Jr. added a 22-yard touchdown run. Miller ran for a pair of two-point conversions, while House had one. 
Shawn Mitchell and Buster Jordan stood out on defense for the Buccaneers.
